  "title": "Items inside a menu that has `withSearchBox` become first in the list after refinement",
  "body": "**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\n1. Go to react-instantsearch [storybook](https://community.algolia.com/react-instantsearch/storybook/?selectedKind=Menu&selectedStory=with%20search%20inside%20items&full=0&down=1&left=1&panelRight=1&downPanel=storybooks%2Fstorybook-addon-knobs)\r\n2. Notice `Textiles & Rugs` is second in the list of items\r\n3. Click `Textiles & Rugs`\r\n4. Notice `Textiles & Rugs` order is changed and now appears first in the list. \r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\nI'd expect the item order to be retained after refinement. At least thats whats happens with menu's that don't have `withSearchBox`.\r\n\r\n--\r\nThank you for this excellent package. ",
